    <p>
      Stock small block motors provide considerable improvements over Jag power. Use a 305 (5.0) for fuel economy or a 350 (5.7) for more punch. Other V8 sizes, 327, 400 (small block) etc. are also suitable. I am definitely pro Hot Rod but I don’t want you to get the idea that you need a high performance motor to motivate that Kitty (the OEM 6 and 12 are 4.2 and 5.3L respectively).
    </p>
  </div>
